[1
Date: Wed, 28 Feb 2001 09:01:39 +0800
From: Ken Lam <lamsk@fommail.med.um.edu.my>

A Correction
------------
I refer to your recent posting about the viral encephalitis case in Negri
Sembilan. As a point of clarification, specimens from the deceased were not
sent to University Hospital for testing as stated in the South China Press
Report. In any case, it should not take more than a day to get preliminary
serology results for Nipah virus or Japanese encephalitis virus infections
and certainly not 2 weeks.
I hope the Ministry of Health Malaysia will provide details of the case.
--
Ken Lam
<lamsk@fommail.med.um.edu.my>
